social_posts.post_text: We're hosting events Thursday, December 1 & Friday, December 2 and will be closed for service. Wanna book an event of your own? Email Nan at events@cassiala.com!
When it gets dark, our patio lights up. We've got blankets and heaters to make sure you stay cozy while enjoying dinner under the stars!

You heard the SWEET news? Rustic Canyon Pastry Chef Erika Chan has curated a special collection of cookies from across our family of restaurants, just in time for the holidays. Each Holiday Cookie Box includes a dozen festive treats like these gorgeous Beets & Berries Oreos from @rusticcanyon alongside Lemongrass Shortbread from our kitchen here at @dinecassia and more!

100% of all proceeds will be donated to one of our favorite non-profits—No Us Without You, a LA-based charity helping undocumented immigrants and their families experiencing food insecurity.

Limited quantities available, so order yours today for pickup at Rustic Canyon on December 18. Tap the link in our bio to order!

social_posts.post_text: 🎵 Oh, the weather outside is frightful, but the fire is so delightful. 🎶

There's still time to join us for a New Year's Eve family-style dinner featuring our menu favorites alongside specials like Vietnamese-Cajun Crawfish Spring Rolls with pickled mustard greens, bamboo shoots, Bibb lettuce, herbs & fish sauce and Honey Walnut Maitake Mushrooms with apples & spiced walnuts. Plus, you can toast the year to come with specialty cocktails and wine flights inspired by New Orleans' neighborhoods. Tap the link in our bio or visit our website to reserve your spot.
It's a comfort food kind of night. Cozy up to this warm Koda Farms Chickpea Curry with coconut milk and cilantro, served with housemade organic clay oven bread.

We're sending up a huge THANK YOU to everyone who purchased our Rustic Canyon Family Holiday Cookie Box! With your help, we were able to raise an incredible $4000 for @nouswithoutyou to continue their important work in our community. We sincerely hope that each bite brought you a little holiday cheer!

The countdown is on to join us for a very special New Year's Eve family-style dinner featuring specials like Black Pepper Udon & Braised Lamb Shank Ragu with Phú Quốc Island black peppercorns, Vietnamese-Cajun Crawfish Spring Rolls with pickled mustard greens, bamboo shoots, Bibb lettuce, herbs & fish sauce and much more. Raise a glass to the year to come with specialty cocktails and wine flights inspired by New Orleans' neighborhoods. Tap the link in our bio or visit our website to reserve your spot.
Taking a break from the booze this Dry January? Enjoy a delicious mocktail, like this Chamomile Sour made with Spiritless Kentucky 74, chamomile and lemon.

Name one thing that sounds more comforting than a warm bowl of Laksa delivered to your door...we'll wait. Rainy days are the perfect excuse to tap the link in our bio or log onto your favorite delivery app and have dinner brought to you this evening!
Uh-oh, it's Friday night and you forgot to make a reservation! No worries, we've got spots at the bar just for walk-ins.
This unbelievably tender Charred Spicy Lamb Breast is bursting with flavor thanks to a blend of Sichuan peppercorn, cumin, sambal and sesame sauce.
Don't be fooled by their size--these Spicy Wontons are packed with huge flavor! Each piece is hand-filled with pork, shrimp, ham, napa cabbage and topped with roasted chile oil.
Your Dry January just got extra refreshing with this zippy Lemongrass Fizz made with Monday 'Gin', lemongrass and fresh lemon.

We’re kicking off the Year of the Rabbit in style this Sunday for our Lunar New Year celebration! Join us for dinner, where we'll be handing out holiday candies and red envelopes, several of which will contain $50 gift cards for lucky guests!

Join us in welcoming the Year of the Rabbit tonight as part of our Lunar New Year celebration! We’re handing out candies and red envelopes during tonight’s service, several of which will contain $50 gift cards for lucky guests!

We are thrilled to share the news that we have been nominated by the James Beard Foundation as a 2023 Semi-Finalist for Outstanding Restaurant! We are honored to be recognized in the company of such incredible peers. We would like to extend our deepest thanks to the heart of our restaurant: our Front & Back of House Staff and our dedicated Management Team, without whom none of this would be possible.

Sunday nights call for something rich and comforting. Lucky for you, we're here with this
Grilled Creekstone Farms Steak Frites. Organic hanger steak with Phu Quoc island peppercorn sauce, shallot butter and crispy, golden French fries.

Enjoy a romantic Valentine's Day dinner at Cassia with luxurious dishes for two—like this Smoked Prime Rib with Scallion-Gruyère Popovers and a Lobster seasoned with chilies, ginger, garlic, black pepper & scallions—alongside a special dessert, themed cocktail and wine flight.

Reservations available now via Resy, with room for walk-ins at the bar. Tap the link in our bio!
We know what you're craving...it's this Kaya Toast with luscious coconut jam, butter and perfectly slow cooked egg. Lucky for you, we open at 5 p.m.

We are proud as can be to be participating in the Uncle Nearest HBCU Old Fashioned Challenge! Now through the end of March, @unclenearest will donate $1 for every Uncle Nearest Old Fashioned sold to Historically Black Colleges & Universities. Their goal is to raise a whopping $1 MILLION dollars--now that's something we can all raise a glass to! Come by to try one of these classic cocktails for a great cause.
Indulge in this rich, luscious Black Truffle Cheese Fondue, made with Sottocenere truffle cheese and black truffles, served with our Clay Oven Bread.

Get ready to mix it up! Our Spicy Minced Duck Dan Dan Noodles are back. Drizzled in sesame-leek sauce with roasted chile oil, pickled mustard greens, scallions and cilantro, these noodles pack some serious flavor.

We still have room available for our luxurious Valentine's Day Dinner. We've got sumptuous specials like Smoked Prime Rib with Scallion-Gruyère Popovers and a Lobster seasoned with chilies, ginger, garlic, black pepper & scallions, plus a special dessert, themed cocktail and wine flight! Tap the link in our bio to reserve. We will also keep room for walk-ins at the bar.

We've got a handful of last-minute reservations available for tonight's Valentine's dinner, plus plenty of walk-in spots at the bar. No fancy set menu - just some really awesome special dishes, drinks and wine flights to share with your loved ones.

Back in 2016, our co-owners Kim Luu-Ng and Chef Bryant Ng founded LA Chefs for Human Rights to benefit and increase awareness of human rights causes that directly affect Angelenos. Over the years, we’ve united some of the city’s best culinary talent, entertainers and human rights activists to raise more than $1.1 million for local non-profits! 

On Monday, April 24, we’re shining a light on @advancingjusticesocal and partnering with them for the LA Chefs Ruby Table fundraiser at Cassia. They’re celebrating their 40th anniversary as the nation’s largest legal and civil rights organization for AAPI.  With the rise in hate and violence towards Asian Americans since the Pandemic, supporting AJSOCAL is a deeply personal and important cause to Kim and Bryant. PLUS, we’re honoring two incredible human rights activists—Lisa Ling and Daniel Wu—for their boldness and leadership in strengthening the AAPI movement. The talented Jeannie Mai Jenkins is emceeing the evening, with a who’s who of AAPI talent from the culinary, film, TV and literary worlds. It’s going to be a magical and powerful night for an amazing cause. If you’d like to show your support, please donate directly to AJSOCAL by visiting the link in bio. 

#lachefsforhumanrights #ajsocal #aapi #asianamerican #40forward

A reminder that we’re closed tonight—Monday, April 24—for the LA Chefs Ruby Table event! Kim Luu-Ng and Chef Bryant Ng’s LA Chefs for Human Rights fundraising platform is partnering with @advancingjusticesocal to benefit the nation’s largest legal and civil rights organization for AAPI and honor award-winning journalist, producer & television host Lisa Ling and celebrated actor, director & producer Daniel Wu. Chef Bryant has also gathered some of LA’s most acclaimed AAPI chefs to cook with him at this invite-only dinner, which includes Niki Nakayama & Carole Iida-Nakayama (n/naka), Shirley Chung (Ms. Chi Café), Jenee Kim (Park’s BBQ), and Bugra Arkin (Dolan’s Uyghur Cuisine). We’re so excited to welcome all of these incredible talent into our home tonight to uplift the AAPI community, and support social justice and civil rights for AAPI and all diverse peoples!

If you’d like to support AJSOCAL, which is turning 40 this year, please donate to them directly by visiting the link in bio. 

#lachefsforhumanrights #ajsocal #aapi #asianamerican #40forward

We’re still glowing from last week’s incredible AJSOCAL LA Chefs Ruby Table event! Kim Luu-Ng and Chef Bryant Ng’s LA Chefs for Human Rights fundraising platform partnered with @advancingjusticesocal, the nation’s largest legal and civil rights organization for AAPI, for this star-studded benefit uniting acclaimed AAPI chefs, community leaders and talent from the entertainment and literary worlds. 

We honored human rights activists Lisa Ling and Daniel Wu with the Ruby Hero Award, and were moved by their powerful speeches and call to keep fighting together against racism and bigotry. Emcee Jeanne Mai Jenkins brought her spirited humor, and The Filharmonic had everyone singing and dancing with their rousing a cappella performance. Bryant cooked an amazing multi-course dinner with chefs Shirley Chung, Niki Nakayama, Carole Iida-Nakayama, Bugra Arkin and Jenee Kim that was pure comfort. Ambassadors for Justice Rosalind Chao, Yoson An, Dawn Lyen-Gardner, Krista Kleiner, Bao Nguyen, Viet Thanh Nguyen and Brandon Tsay worked the room, lending their strong influence and support to this very important cause. Of course, we couldn’t have pulled this off without our rockstar Cassia colleagues, the team from AJSOCAL and our generous sponsors. While AAPI Heritage Month is every month in our books, if you’d like to support the AAPI community, you can make a direct donation to AJSOCAL through the link in our bio. 

#lachefsforhumanrights #ajsocal #aapi #asianamerican #40forward

The Spice Table Burger is here! Starting this month, we’ll feature monthly specials available for dine-in and we’d thought it would be nice to kick this off with a legendary one. Before Chef Bryant Ng and Kim Luu-Ng opened Cassia, they ran The Spice Table, a critically-acclaimed restaurant in DTLA that sadly closed because of the Metro coming in.

We’re serving up The Spice Table Burger with spicy cumin fries all-month-long so dig into this with a nice, craft beer and stay tuned to see what’s coming to the menu next month!

In case you missed it the Spice Table Burger is back on the menu BUT only for the month of November. 

Here's a message from Bryant on why he decided to bring it to the Cassia menu for a limited time: 
"Back in 2013, when I first cooked this burger at The Spice Table, many fancy restaurants were making fancy burgers.  If you can remember that far back, they were stuffed with foie gras and truffles and looked like creations only a fancy chef could create in their dreams.  I wanted to do the opposite. Not to be different, but because that's who I am.  I wanted a burger that looked like a burger.  I wanted to use Kraft American cheese.  I wanted it to taste like nostalgia, but slightly different.  You didn't need to know why it was different, it just needed to taste good and remind you of something.  So I looked at burgers I love: In-n-out (Animal style with chopped chiles...of course), Pie-n-Burger (add onions and heavy on the seasoning), and Apple Pan's Hickory burger (as is). 

The love for these burgers is what led to The Spice Table Cheeseburger.  Like everyone, I love smash burgers because of the awesome caramelization and crust the meat forms on the griddle.  I chose instead to cook it on the grill for that slight smokey flavor you get, while cooking over really hot coals to give it that caramelization and crust.  It's not as crusty as the smash (and we all love crusty), but you get smokiness from the open flames.  Back then Jonathan Gold (RIP) called it one of his top 10 burgers in LA...I miss him.  Besha Rodell (then at LA Weekly) called it the best "low brow" burger which I took as a huge compliment...because she understood what I was trying to do.  I brought it back to Cassia (and only for 1 month, November) to remind me and our staff of where we came from and that keeping it simple may just be the best way."

For those of you that LOVED the Spice Table Burger, you’ve got just 2 more nights to enjoy it! Most importantly though, there’s more to come, because next up for our monthly dine-in specials is the legendary Vietnamese Pot-Au-Feu — hitting the menu on December 1st! 

The pot-au-feu at Cassia is at first glance indistinguishable from the classic French version — the enduring symbol of French heart and home. 

Short ribs are simmered in broth, potatoes and carrots, a marrowbone jutting from the tureen and even a little dish of mustard, but it is served in a Chinese sandy pot. The consommé is clear and strong, but it is scented with the burnt onion, cinnamon and star anise of a Vietnamese pho (which was probably in some way derived from the colonial pot-au-feu in the first place). In place of coarse salt and cornichons are chopped Vietnamese herbs. This is yet another dish the late Jonathan Gold praised Chef/Owner Bryant Ng interpretation as “claiming the essence of French cooking as his own—colonizing the colonizers at last.”
